<font color="#FF0000">TO VIETSON ON AMERASIANS</font><br>
<tt>Sat Jun 14 22:52:37 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Vietson,<br><br>
In poking around my own mind on this issue of discrimination, of which this seems to be upon final distillation, it strikes me that what we see is a learned behavior.<br><br>
No human child is born with prejudice as genetic memory of their race or culture. Unlike the baby spider that can spin a web without the slightest instruction, we learn our behavior from those who raise and nurture us from infancy.<br><br>
The discrimination experienced by Amerasians was destined to occur long before there were any.<br><br>
I agree with you that it is our conscience upon which we must depend to fight this ugly mess...on both sides.<br><br>
That is really the only &quot;solution&quot;.<br><br>
My heart goes out to all children victims of war.<br><br>
They really didn't ask for it.<br><br>
They just got stuck with it. <br><br>
It is up to all of us to try to do something about it.
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


